The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Sunday, December 21, 2003 				 Mob fury follows road mishap
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Asansol, Dec. 20: A 27-year-old motorcyclist died on the spot when he was run over by a minibus this morning near National Highway 2.																								Residents of Kalipahari took to the streets to protest the death of Virendra Dokania, who was coming from Kalipahari railway station.																								The residents blocked the highway for more than an hour and also tried to set two minibuses on fire. The mob even tried to prevent the police from removing the body. The police had to resort to a lathicharge to disperse the crowd.																								Residents demanded a permanent traffic police posting in Kalipahari. Asansol additional superintendent of police Pallab Kanti Ghosh said that the demand would be considered.																								Jamuria municipality chairman Tapas Kabi, who rushed to the spot, said: We will place our demand for a traffic police posting in the area with senior district police officials.																								In another incident, 11 passengers were injured when a bus collided head on with a truck near Kajora railway crossing under Andal police station, 160 km from Calcutta. 
